Atomsk can offer options to duplicate atomic systems, introduce defects, construct crystals and polycrystals
  Atomsk employs Voronoi tessellation method
For running, you need to run "Windows PowerShell"
  Examples are here: https://atomsk.univ-lille.fr/doc/en/mode_create.html, try Examples on the Windows PowerShell
  Once file generated, you can find the location by searching the file name
    For my case, data are stored in Jungwan Lee
  When you copy-paste to excel, it will show up the data

(1) LAMMPS (Large-scale Atomic/Molecular Massively Parallel Simulator)
a code performing simulations on classical particles -including, but not restricted to, molecular dynamics
LAMMPS calculation is controlled by a script file, often called "in.something"
